<item>
            <title>[HIVE-10219] BytesBytesMultiHashMap::clear() can&apos;t be concurrently used with reads</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-10219</link>
                <project id="12310843" key="HIVE">Hive</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The semantics of the HashMap::clear() is unclear for concurrent access.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;With &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HIVE-10128&quot; title=&quot;BytesBytesMultiHashMap does not allow concurrent read-only access&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HIVE-10128&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HIVE-10128&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; fixes, the only remaining thread-safety concern is the behaviour of clear() calls.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Concurrent usage + clearing from HybridHash and VectorMapJoin operator will result in race conditions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is no valid clear() operations possible without knowledge of the cached nature and the ref-count of each hashtable.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
